Docker container to build ariane core and plugins

* Build

sudo docker build -t echinopsii/ariane.buildenv .


* Run 

An helper script is provided here : https://github.com/echinopsii/net.echinopsii.docker.base/tree/master/ariane.buildenv/run.sh

```
$ ./run.sh  
Usage : ./run.sh [LOCAL ARIANE SOURCE DIR] [DISTRIB COMMAND]
```

** Example 

```
./run.sh /ECHINOPSII/DEV -h
```

```
./run.sh /ECHINOPSII/DEV "ditpkgr master.SNAPSHOT"
```

```
./run.sh /ECHINOPSII/DEV "pluginpkgr ariane.community.plugin.rabbitmq master.SNAPSHOT master.SNAPSHOT"
```










/ECHINOPSII must be mounted
  * Ariane repositories will be cloned in this dir
  * zip files will be generated in the artifacts subdirectory of this dir
  * You can change this directory to another one (you need to change the -v option as well as the docker cmd)

$HOME/.m2 can also be mountedito avoid redownloading dependencies at each build


** Example

sudo docker run --rm \
     --privileged=true \ #IF SELINUX
     -e ARIANE_DISTRIB_ARGS="distpkgr master.SNAPSHOT" \
     -v /ECHINOPSII/DEV:/ECHINOPSII:rw -v /home/mffrench/.m2:/home/mffrench/.m2:rw \
     echinopsii/ariane.buildenv:<USERNAME>

sudo docker run --rm \ 
     --privileged=true \ #IF SELINUX
     -e ARIANE_DISTRIB_ARGS="pluginpkgr ariane.community.plugin.rabbitmq master.SNAPSHOT master.SNAPSHOT" \
     -v /ECHINOPSII/DEV:/ECHINOPSII:rw -v /home/mffrench/.m2:/home/mffrench/.m2:rw \
     echinopsii/ariane.buildenv:<USERNAME>
